## What Changed

The triumvirate relocation decision (option B) was made in Session 89: **Gardener's canonical home is Minder**, not a hub-resident advisor or the superseded wheel-power standalone spoke.

- Hub scripts `verify_health.py` and `scan_characteristics.py` remain operational as **interim** implementations only
- Two Minder lugs created to track the Minder-native rebuild: `task-minder-gardener-health-verification-v1` and `task-minder-gardener-characteristics-scan-v1`
- Hub KB epic (`epic-hub-kb-system-expediter-gardener-v1`) Expediter/Librarian phases remain hub-owned and unaffected

## Why It Matters

Any hub session planning to implement or extend Gardener advisor logic should treat hub-resident Gardener scripts as temporary. Building Gardener features in the hub would create migration debt. The canonical build target is Minder Phase 2+.

## Migration Instructions

1. Do not add new features to `WAI-Hub/advisors/gardener/verify_health.py` or `scan_characteristics.py`
2. When Minder Gardener equivalents go live, retire hub scripts
3. Hub KB epic Expediter/Librarian phases can proceed independently — they have no Gardener dependency

